{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "As this auxiliary decoder is used solely for feature learning, it is omitted at inference time to avoid unnecessary computation and maintain efficiency.",
    "Experiments DatasetsWe evaluate our method on two benchmark datasets for 3D occupancy prediction: Occ3D-nuScenes [39] and Sur-roundOcc dataset [43].",
    "Both datasets represent the scene as a voxel grid of size 200 × 200 × 16, where each voxel is labeled as either occupied or empty, and occupied voxels are further categorized into 16 semantic classes such as car and pedestrian.",
    "Occ3D-nuScenes defines the voxel grid in the ego coordinate, spanning [-40m, 40m] along both X and Y and [-1m, 5.4m] along Z, discretized at a resolution of 0.4m, with occupied voxels assigned to 17 semantic classes (16 known categories + others).",
    "Sur-roundOcc dataset, in contrast, defines the voxel grid in the LiDAR coordinate, covering [-50m, 50m] along X and Y and [-5m, 3m] along Z, with a voxel resolution of 0.5m."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Experiments DatasetsWe evaluate our method on two benchmark datasets for 3D occupancy prediction: Occ3D-nuScenes [39] and Sur-roundOcc dataset [43]."
  ]
}